Legionellosis - Spain (8) 19961215.2080
Date: Tue, 17 Oct 2000 18:30:34 WST
From: Denis Green <snoigel@hotmail.com>
Source: El Pais 17 Oct 2000 & earlier despatches
[in Spanish, translated & abstracted by Mod.JW

Vigo (Galicia): 26 suspect cases (including 2 deaths) of atypical
pneumonia, the last with onset 5 Oct 2000, linked to a circumscribed area in
the town center which includes the Hospital Xeral de Vigo. Jose Maria
Hernandez Cochon, Health Counsellor for Galicia, stated that one of the 10
cases on which tests had been made was confirmed by the Institute of
Toxicology as due to _Legionella_, with 4 cases negative & 5 still under test.
The source has not been identified; the air conditioning system of the
hospital is under suspicion, but has not been shut down.
Arbizu (Navarra): 5 cases of pneumonia, with onsets on 2 Oct 2000 (1 case),
11 Oct 2000 (3 cases) & 13 Oct 2000 (1 case). All are users of a sports
complex 30 km east of Pamplona. The complex, which has a pool, jacuzzi &
sauna which are under suspicion as the source(s), was closed on 13 Oct 2000
for 2-3 weeks for disinfection.
